# Shared Task Tracking

- Do not use internal Cursor-managed todo or task lists as the source of truth.
- If a checklist, handoff, or task tracker is needed, keep it on disk in the repository so other agents can read and update it.
- Prefer a normal markdown file such as `plan.md` or a task-specific file under `docs/` when tracking progress.
- When a shared task list exists, update that file as work progresses instead of maintaining a separate hidden list.
